    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-22T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-22T14:00:00-05:00" n="305"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/9–2251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Turkey</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d305fn1">Message drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MCR1"
                            >Moore</persName>. A marginal note reads: “Background statement cleared
                        with: Defense—Col <persName>Newland</persName>, White House—Mr.
                            <persName>Tubby</persName>, <gloss target="#t_RA1">RA</gloss>—Mr.
                            <persName corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName>.” Repeated to the
                        Embassies in Egypt, Greece, the United Kingdom, and France.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-22T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 22, 1951—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. Re <hi rend="italic">NY Times</hi> art Sept 22 stating Pres <persName
                        corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> has assigned <persName corresp="#p_HWA1"
                        >Harriman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BON1">Bradley</persName> to
                    prepare way for earliest inclusion Greece and Turkey in <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> and referring to their departure for Europe and Near East
                    within ten days. Info along following lines being given for background and not
                    for attribution in response to press inquiries: In the course of discussions of
                    the North Atlantic Council in Ottawa it was suggested that the US, UK and France
                    send military representatives to Turkey and Greece for preliminary discussions
                    of their participation in the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> (after
                    ratification by the present members of their inclusion). The possibility of the
                    US sending such a representative is now being considered and if one goes it will
                    probably be General <persName corresp="#p_BON1">Bradley</persName>. There are no
                    present plans for Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> to go to
                    Turkey or Greece.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
